<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97984863227284></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97984863227284><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97984863227284>RE: why be a roge</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97984863227284#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=21407><span id= >Jest</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 18th 8:12 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Why be a rogue?&nbsp;&nbsp;We are the most athletic class in the game.  Rogues need to be strong, have good eye and hand coordination (dexterity), and agile.  Also, we are the definition of cool. We're Back in Black and we Listen to the Money Talk.  You don't choose a rogue to become almighty and powerful.  I chose a rogue because I can be my sarcastic and a jack@#@ and then call it roleplaying.  It fits my personality.<br>&nbsp;<br>Jest Acestalker<br>Assistant Guildmaster of Dark Hour on Solusek Ro</td></tr>
